VI. Conclusion
In this paper we set out to see whether recent tax reform effortsat the federal,state, andlocal levels havebeen effectivein alleviating tax burdens on the poor. Although the taxation of the poor is frequentlydiscussed, both conceptualand practicalmeasurementproblems have resultedin few attemptsto determinethe overalltax burdensfaced by poor individualsand families. Using a microsimulationmodel of the majorfederal, state, and local personaltaxes, we have shown that lowincome families in New York and Massachusettsface tax burdensof 18 percent of income in New York and 15 percent in Massachusetts.The
